ChatModel.doChat(ChatRequest) is the override point for test doubles — not chat(ChatRequest)

## The technique

When implementing a test `ChatModel` without mocks (because `AiMessage`/`ChatResponse` have final methods), override `doChat(ChatRequest)` — not `chat(ChatRequest)`:

```java
ChatModel testModel = new ChatModel() {
    @Override
    public ChatResponse doChat(final ChatRequest request) {
        // inspect request, return appropriate response
        return ChatResponse.builder()
                .aiMessage(new AiMessage("{...json...}"))
                .build();
    }
};
```

`chat(ChatRequest)` is a **default method** in the `ChatModel` interface that calls `chat(ChatRequest, ChatRequestOptions)`, which then calls `doChat(ChatRequest)`. The chain applies listeners, merges request parameters, and fires `onRequest`/`onResponse` hooks. By overriding `doChat()`, the test skips the listener chain and returns directly.

`casehub-engine-api`'s `Agent.execute()` calls `model.chat(request)` which eventually reaches `doChat()`.

## Why this is non-obvious

`chat(ChatRequest)` and `chat(ChatRequest, ChatRequestOptions)` are the visible API methods that developers see in IDE autocompletion. `doChat(ChatRequest)` is buried as an implementation detail — a `default` method with a `throw new RuntimeException("Not implemented")` body that exists specifically as the override target. The JavaDoc doesn't prominently surface this as the intended extension point for test doubles.

**See also:** [GE-20260618-5008f5](../casehub-engine/GE-20260618-5008f5.md) — @Alternative @Priority(10) CDI test bean avoids Quarkus CDI restart (related CDI testing technique)

IntelliJ 2023.2: testParameterInfo() absent — use MockCreateParameterInfoContext instead

### Symptom
`myFixture.testParameterInfo()` causes `NoSuchMethodError` or is unavailable in IntelliJ 2023.2 when testing a custom `ParameterInfoHandler`.

### Context
Testing a `ParameterInfoHandler<PsiElement, MyBuiltin>` for a custom language in a `BasePlatformTestCase` with `intellijIdeaCommunity("2023.2")` in build.gradle.kts.

### Fix
Use `MockCreateParameterInfoContext` from `com.intellij.testFramework.utils.parameterInfo`:

```java
import com.intellij.testFramework.utils.parameterInfo.MockCreateParameterInfoContext;

myFixture.configureByText("Foo.java",
    "... typeArgList(1, <caret>i, 'T') ...");
MyParameterInfoHandler handler = new MyParameterInfoHandler();
MockCreateParameterInfoContext ctx =
    new MockCreateParameterInfoContext(myFixture.getEditor(), myFixture.getFile());
PsiElement element = handler.findElementForParameterInfo(ctx);
if (element != null) {
    handler.showParameterInfo(element, ctx);
    assertNotNull(ctx.getItemsToShow());
}
```

### Why This Is Non-Obvious
`testParameterInfo()` is the documented approach in IntelliJ plugin SDK examples. `MockCreateParameterInfoContext` is in the test framework jar but absent from official docs. Its availability and API differ by platform version — this pattern works in 2023.2 but the equivalent `testParameterInfo()` method appears only in later platform versions.

assertThat(captor.getValue().inReplyTo()).isEqualTo(42L);
    }
}
```

